cs|1|at|
^-{ Leading from an unbid 3-card suit headed by a 2-card honor sequence (like the AK, KQ, 
 QJ, J10, or 109) is much more attractive against a trump contract than it is against notrump. }

|
pg| ***** 459 ***** |


cs|3|at|{ A singleton is about the worst opening lead that you can make against notrump (unless 
 your partner bid that suit), but it is one of the best opening leads against a trump contract. }

|
pg| ***** 460 ***** |


cs|2|at|{ While a side suit singleton is usually an attractive opening lead against a trump contract,
 if you are dealt 4 or more trumps, playing the forcing game is often better for the defense. }

|
