at|This suggests that the forcing game may be an effective defense. If you can force the declarer to ruff a couple of times, you may be able to gain trump control. Your length and strength in hearts suggests that hearts is the suit of choice if you want to try to force the declarer to ruff. One of the nice things about this hand is that you rate to be on lead again. If the forcing game does not seem to be working, you will have another chance to lead your singleton!|
