at|^-Our study of opening leads is just about finished now and, after you complete the remaining exercises in this chapter, we will move on to study other aspects of defense at bridge.

Give yourself a pat on the back for having completed this first chapter because the study of opening leads is one of the most complex and challenging aspects of bridge. In fact, entire books have been written about opening leads and it would be possible to dedicate an entire program the size of this one to that subject.

The opening lead is arguably the most important card played by the defenders in the course of a bridge deal, but it is still only 1 of the 26 cards that they will play. After the following quizzes, we will turn our attention to the other 25 cards that the defenders play.
|
